(2, 'DSCE Forum for Equity: On Challenges Facing Math & Physics', '&lt;p class=&quot;col d-flex f-d-vertical align-center col-8 col-m-10 col-xs-12&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 66.6667%; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; align-self: auto; -webkit-box-flex: 1; flex: 1 1 66.67%; -webkit-box-orient: vertical; -webkit-box-direction: normal; flex-direction: column; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;p item=&quot;content&quot; class=&quot;event-rich-text-block _w-max-675 w-richtext&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); max-width: 675px;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 1.15vw; font-family: calluna, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.55;&quot;&gt;DSCE alumni are invited to join MIT alumni for a virtual discussion addressing challenges facing traditionally underrepresented populations in math and physics.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 1.15vw; font-family: calluna, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.55;&quot;&gt;Presented by the MIT Alumni Association, the MIT Forum for Equity aims to engage alumni through thoughtful online conversations that help educate, inform, and examine the problems focused on social justice and help to catalyze change in our communities and in the world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 1.15vw; font-family: calluna, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.55;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Jim Gates, PhD&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a theoretical physicist. He is currently the Brown Theoretical Physics Center Director, Ford Foundation Professor of Physics, Affiliate Mathematics Professor, and a Watson Institute for International Studies &amp;amp; Public Affairs Faculty Fellow at Brown University. He is known for his work on supersymmetry, supergravity, and superstring theory.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 1.15vw; font-family: calluna, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.55;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Edray Herber Goins, PhD (BS &rsquo;94)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is Professor of Mathematics at Pomona College. The product of the Los Angeles Unified (LAUSD) public school system, he attended the California Institute of Technology, where he majored in mathematics and physics, and earned his doctorate in mathematics from Stanford University. Dr. Goins has held positions at the world&amp;#x2019;s premiere research institutions, including the National Security Agency in Ft. Meade, Maryland; the Mathematical Sciences Research Institute in Berkeley, California; the Institute for Advanced Study in Princeton, New Jersey; the Max Planck Institute for Mathematics in Bonn, Germany; Harvard University in Cambridge, Massachusetts; and the California Institute of Technology in Pasadena, California. In January 2004 he was featured in Black Issues in Higher Education as one of the &quot;2004 Emerging Scholars of the Year.&rdquo; From 2004-2018, Dr. Goins was a professor of mathematics at Purdue University in West Lafayette, Indiana.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;col col-12&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; align-self: auto; -webkit-box-flex: 1; flex-grow: 1; flex-shrink: 1; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;button-wrapper d-flex justify-center&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 1.5vw; margin-bottom: 1.5vw; -webkit-box-pack: center; justify-content: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://encompass.alum.mit.edu/s/1314/17form/interior.aspx?cid=91351&amp;amp;gid=13&amp;amp;pgid=55680&amp;amp;sid=1314&quot; class=&quot;button-primary w-button&quot; style=&quot;background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: reason-new, sans-serif; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-line: none; display: block; padding: 1rem 2.25rem; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 88, 81); line-height: 1.2; cursor: pointer; border-radius: 0px; position: relative; inset: auto; z-index: auto; overflow: visible; min-width: 60px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: auto; margin-left: auto; clear: none; -webkit-box-orient: horizontal; -webkit-box-direction: normal; flex-flow: row nowrap; -webkit-box-pack: center; justify-content: center; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; -webkit-box-flex: 1; flex: 1 1 0%; gap: 0px; transition: all 250ms cubic-bezier(0.455, 0.03, 0.515, 0.955) 0s; font-size: 0.9rem; object-fit: fill; align-self: auto; font-feature-settings: &amp;quot;salt&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;Register Now&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 3, '2020-10-15 15:20:51'),
(3, 'Welcome to the Computer Forum! ', '&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(46, 45, 41); font-family: &amp;quot;Source Sans Pro&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 21px; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;The DSCE Computer Forum is a cooperative venture that encourages collaboration between the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://cs.stanford.edu/&quot; class=&quot;su-link su-link--external&quot; data-extlink=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 108, 184); text-decoration: inherit; font-weight: 600; font-family: &amp;quot;Source Sans Pro&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 21px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Computer Scien&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(46, 45, 41); font-family: &amp;quot;Source Sans Pro&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 21px; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://ee.stanford.edu/&quot; class=&quot;su-link su-link--external&quot; data-extlink=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(0, 108, 184); text-decoration: inherit; font-weight: 600; font-family: &amp;quot;Source Sans Pro&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 21px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Electrical Engineering&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(46, 45, 41); font-family: &amp;quot;Source Sans Pro&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 21px; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Departments at Stanford, and 60+ companies located in Silicon Valley, the rest of the U.S., Asia, and Europe. The Forum provides a mechanism for developing interaction with industrial researchers and their academic counterparts, promoting the exchange of the most advanced technological ideas in fields of computer science and electrical engineering. The Forum also offers industry the opportunity to become familiar with the professional abilities and interests of DSCE students through its active recruiting program.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;', 3, '2020-10-15 15:22:30'),
(4, 'Topic by DSCE Management Company - Healthcare Innovation and Investment Forumin', '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; height: inherit; background-color: rgb(250, 248, 249);&quot;&gt;With the economic development in the last decade, China has the potential from an innovation sponge - absorbing and adapting global technology and knowledge - to an innovation leader. Remarkable progresses have been made in some industries, greatly serving domestic demand and even impacting other countries. Healthcare sector is a strong player in the trend, including healthcare services, medical equipment and devices, pharmaceuticals, biotechnology and related life sciences. At this exclusive forum, more than 80 VC/PE investors, executives and entrepreneurs in healthcare industry are invited to join, half of whom are expectedly Harvard alumni. You will experience an interactive sharing modeled after the Harvard Business School&rsquo;s case discussion method on the following three topics.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;table style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; border-spacing: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 248, 249);&quot;&gt;&lt;tbody style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;tr style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; height: inherit; background-color: rgb(250, 248, 249);&quot;&gt;- Investment in healthcare innovation and entrepreneurship in China&lt;br&gt;- Cross-border healthcare technology and business model transfer&lt;br&gt;- From ventures to enterprises: growing healthcare business in China&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2020-10-16 08:31:45');

